{
  "stem": "18470.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You can try to expunge them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But somehow they're embedded in the psyche of the people, which is a very frightening thing about these kinds of incidents.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, and there was, as we know, in the Rhineland itself over the course of the centuries, horrendous episodes of murder, pillage, and rape against Jews on a periodic basis into the 20th century-- with, you know, periods from the Weimar Republic on to the origins of Nazism over a short span of less than a decade.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, my grandmother, Henrietta Gerson, was elected mayor of Oberwesel in the late 1920s, which was rather remarkable; first of all, to have a woman as mayor, and secondly to have a Jewish woman as mayor.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But she, by reputation, was one of the brightest people in town.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she had her term.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think also the fact that they had lost two sons who died for the fatherland, so to speak, that made a difference.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But in the end, with the rise of Nazism, nothing that Jews had done for their country-- because they saw themselves as German citizens-- made any difference.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were singled out not because they were German Jews, but because they were Jews irrespective of the Germanness of-- of their life.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the fact that my grandmother had been the mayor of Oberwesel, and that her two boys were killed fighting for Kaiser Wilhelm on the Eastern Front, in the end it made no difference.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You were three years old when Adolf Hitler came to power, which means that your-- your grammar schooling was-- took place during the early Nazi period.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What was it like to be a Jewish boy in the schools of Oberwesel at that time?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I don't-- I remember only my expulsion.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
